The paper deals with the analysis of complex networks using graph mining techniques. Specifically, it focuses on the detection of motifs in networks and investigates their distribution in various systems. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including social networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), network analysis (cs.NI), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SD). However, given the emphasis on graph mining and motif detection, we believe that cs.SI and cs.SD are the most likely categories, followed by cs.NI, cs.DS, and cs.LG.
